      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Ledger, 1865-1866, containing the accounts of Brownley and
         Miller, a general store located in Gloucester County,
         Virginia. At the front of the ledger, there are cash accounts
         for money paid to employees and other store expenses. The
         ledger also contains barter accounts and customer accounts
         that include the customer's name, the date of the sale, type
         of transaction or item purchased, and the amount. At the back
         of the ledger, there are accounts concerning boots and shoes
         received in the shop. There are 85 blank ledger pages.</p>
      </scopecontent>
